The Union of Galway was created with 21 EDs in 1849 but absorbed part of a proposed Union named Cossaun almost immediately and is shown as having 26 EDs in 1861. This entity is the one that absorbed 5 EDs almost immediately after its initial creation.
Tuam and Loughrea absorbed the remainder of the proposed Cossaun Union.
